# Agentic Template (stack-agnostic)

Cursor rules, skills, handoff protocol, and test discipline. **Not** tied to a specific stack — document your toolchain in AGENT_HANDOFF.md and TEST_PLAN.md.

Source of truth: PM_PLAN.md, AGENT_HANDOFF.md; .cursor/skills/ (DEV_GUIDE, TEST_TDD, DESIGN_SYSTEM, techwriter, tester, code-reviewer, tech-debt-evaluator, pm-governance, ui-ux, game-readiness, visual-match). Use techwriter for docs; use tester + .cursor/rules/testing.mdc for black-box tests. **TDD:** Read TEST_TDD.md and tester skill first; write a failing test before production code where applicable. **Handoff:** When the user wants a handoff, run code review (code-reviewer), tech debt (tech-debt-evaluator), and your project’s test/coverage commands as documented in AGENT_HANDOFF.md; record in the handoff note. See AGENT_HANDOFF.md and .cursor/rules/handoff-checklist.mdc — do not skip.

**Flutter / iOS apps:** Use [FlutterAgenticTemplate](https://github.com/pbuckles22/FlutterAgenticTemplate) — same agentic layer plus a Flutter iOS-only scaffold.
